Slowly, this government has crept into desuetude. Carthage's politicians are complacent and fat, and her Judges meek and uninspired. It would take little for the government to collapse and fall pray to some foreign despot. That is why we must revitilise the power of the Suffetes, and guarantee the security of our democratic Magistrate Lords.[NEWLINE]
